#Origins of Hot Chocolate
1. It started in Mexico in 500 BC, made from ground-up cocoa seeds mixed with water, cornmeal, and chilli peppers[^1]
2. It made it's way to Europe and when it made it to Spain the drink started to become more like it was today[^2]
3. Hot chocolate today is now more attainable than ever, it is sweet and delicious and a household staple
[^1] It was a very different version of hot chocolate today
[^2] They made it more sweet and hot
[An Abridged History of Hot Chocolate] (https://www.thespruceeats.com/the-history-of-hot-chocolate-764463)
